istical data of such nature. We process this data on the basis of our legitimate interest in understanding the needs and wishes of our customers better so as to properly develop our business, to meet the needs of our customers, and to provide a qualitative, functional and user-friendly service.</p> <p>We collect this information using Google Analytics and Facebook Pixel tools, which enable recording and analysis of the aforementioned data.</p> <p>Here you can find more information on how Google Analytics works and what information is allowed to be collected and analysed by this tool – <a target="_blank" href="https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/1012034?hl=lten&ref_topic=6157800">https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/1012034?hl=lten&ref_topic=6157800</a></p> <p>If you want to disable “Google Analytics” function of your data collection, you can do it at any time following the steps described here: <a target="_blank" href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout/">https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout/</a>.</p> <h4>What are cookies?</h4> <p>A cookie is a small data file that a website saves on your device when you visit it. It is what most websites do. Saved cookies allow the website to remember your actions and selected settings (for example, the language, font size) for some time. This ensures more convenient use of the website, since you do not need to repeatedly enter options when visiting a website or browsing through individual pages.</p> <h4>What cookies do we use and why do we use them?</h4> <p>Our website uses cookies that collect your IP address and browsing information, such as visited websites or time spent on each website. This allows the website to remember your system and settings, thus ensuring a proper and convenient operation of the website.</p> <p>Other cookies allow tracking website traffic and user behaviour on the website. These cookies are installed for the purpose of the aforementioned analysis of visitor behaviour, and to improve the experience of visiting the website. These cookies are installed and used with Google Analytics tool.</p> <p>Cookies are installed on your device only in cases where you give your consent, except for those cookies that are strictly necessary for the technical operation of the website. If you do not give your consent to installing cookies, some of the functions on the website may be partially or completely inactive.</p> <p>We use cookies based on our legitimate interest in ensuring proper functioning of the website. In cases where we use cookies to perform statistics, the legal basis for the use of cookies is your consent.</p> <h4>How to manage cookies?</h4> <p>You can delete all cookies on your device at any time, what is more, there are settings in most browsers to prevent them from installing cookies. You can find out more about your options here:  <a target="_blank" href="http://www.youronlinechoices.com/">http://www.youronlinechoices.com/</a>.</p> <p>However, after deleting cookies some services and functions may not work, you may also need to reset the website settings.</p> <h4>Marketing</h4> <p>We also use the collected data on visitor statistics, visitor traffic, interests and demographic trends for our targeted advertising. We estimate which products you might be interested in based on the results of the analysis. We divide individuals into groups according to the identified attributes and provide targeted advertising to similar groups of people. This process when you see online advertising tailored to your activity is performed via profiling. We do this based on our legitimate interest in achieving effective advertising results and business development.</p> <h4>Your questions and comments</h4> <p>You have an opportunity to ask questions and write comments at some places on the website. We process the details of your statements in order to provide answers to your questions and respond to your opinions. The legal basis for processing this data is our legitimate interest in ensuring the proper quality of the services provided. </p> <h4>Who has access to your data</h4> <p>Access to the data collected on the website is provided to website owner.</p> <p>Also, access to the data may be available to, or the data may be obtained by our partners who provide website content management tools, website hosting services, marketing services. Please note that such entities may only view and process your data to provide us with the services we purchase.</p> <p>The Google Analytics tool is provided by Google Inc., a company operating in the US. Google Inc. is obligated to apply the principles of EU-US Privacy Shield, which ensure that the service provider complies with the requirements of EU privacy standards. This provider is also contractually obliged to ensure privacy. For more information visit: <a target="_blank" href="https://www.google.com/analytics/terms/dpa/dataprocessingamendment_20160909.html">https://www.google.com/analytics/terms/dpa/dataprocessingamendment_20160909.html</a>.</p> <h4>How long your data is stored</h4> <p>We use and store the data collected on the website up to 3 years, the data required for issuing invoices is stored until demand to delete them.</p> <p>Cookies are usually valid for a short period (up to several hours), but in some cases it may take up to 2 years.</p> <h4>Your rights and how you can exercise them</h4> <p>As regards your data which is processed, you have the right to get acquainted with your personal data which is processed; request to correct your personal data; request to delete your personal data; cancel the given consent for the use of cookies by deleting cookies or by disabling them through your browser settings or clicking on either of the following links:</p> <ul> <li><a target="_blank" href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout/">https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout/</a></li> <li><a target="_blank" href="http://www.youronlinechoices.com/">http://www.youronlinechoices.com/</a></li> </ul> <p>You also have the right to request that the processing of your personal data would be restricted or to declare that you do not agree that your personal data would be processed in accordance with our legitimate interest. However, these rights may not be exercised if the particular situation does not meet all the necessary conditions. In this case, we will inform you in detail about the reasons for non-exercise of the right.</p> <p>You can exercise your rights by contacting us by <a href="mailto:info@remapas.lt">info@remapas.lt</a></p> <h4>The right to file a complaint</h4> <p>If you think that we process your personal data improperly or your privacy is violated, you can file a complaint to the State Data Protection Inspectorate, A. Juozapavičiaus str 6, 09310 Vilnius, tel (8 5) 271 2804, 279 1445, fax (8 5) 261 9494, email <a href="mailto:ada@ada.lt">ada@ada.lt</a>.</p>',
